<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-8423] Private and protected inner classes have incorrect access modifier values</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8423</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; java.lang.reflect.Modifier           
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Foo {                                 
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Private {}
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;protected&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Protected {}

    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; void test() {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; Modifier.isPrivate(Private.&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class.&lt;/span&gt;getModifiers()) \\ 0
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; Modifier.isProtected(Protected.&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class.&lt;/span&gt;getModifiers()) \\ 1
    }            
}                                           
Foo.test()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The test above fails (on both assertions). This appears to be due to the ACC_PRIVATE and ACC_PROTECTED modifiers being removed/replaced for inner classes, as well as from their inner class table entries (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6357&quot; title=&quot;Inner classes in Groovy should have the same access modifiers as in Java&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-6357&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-6357&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). Though those modifiers aren&apos;t valid for the classes themselves, they are allowed in the inner classes table (&lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jvms/se7/html/jvms-4.html#jvms-4.7.6&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jvms/se7/html/jvms-4.html#jvms-4.7.6&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
